<reg_short_dscr>:
Physical interface control
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
This register configures critical interface parameters, it is constructed so that it can always be written correctly no matter the current state of the interface. When initializing a physical interface, then this is the first register that must be written, the state of the interface at that point may be unknown and therefore the following scheme is required to bring the interface to a known state:
When writing a 4-bit value to this field construct a 32-bit data-word as follows: a) copy the 4-bit value into bits 3:0, 11:8, 19:16, and 27:24. b) reverse the 4-bit value and copy into bits 7:4, 15:12, 23:20, and 31:28. Example: To write the value 2 to this field; the 32-bit data-word to write is "0x42424242".
Bit 0 configures endianness, 0:Little-Endian, 1:Big-Endian (default).
Bit 1 configures bit-order, 0:MSB-first (default), 1:LSB-first.
Bit 2,3 are reserved and should be kept 0.
